# Copy to .env — never commit real secrets.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Optional: API base for other admin features (defaults to localhost:3000 in code)
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Password reset emails are sent by the Supabase Edge Function `forgot-password` (Resend).
# Set these in the Supabase Dashboard → Edge Functions → Secrets (not in this file):
#   RESEND_API_KEY
#   FRONTEND_RESET_PASSWORD_WEB_URL = full base, e.g. https://your-staging-site.com/reset-password
#   FRONTEND_RESET_PASSWORD_URL      = app deep-link base for mobile (never used for web if it looks Expo/app-only)
#   WEB_RESET_ALLOWED_ORIGINS       = comma-separated https origins for web reset links from the browser, e.g. https://app.example.com
#   RESET_FROM_EMAIL, RESEND_FROM_EMAIL, FROM_EMAIL — after the clinic verifies their domain in Resend,
#     set these to the same “from” (e.g. Floora HEP <noreply@clinicdomain.com>) so all users get mail, not only the Resend account email.
#
# Local admin web: the app sends reset_web_base from the browser (localhost) so emails are not stuck on Expo :8081.
